t\n  cubit.emit(cubit.state.copyWith(\n      serverBaseUrl: \'http://localhost:3
000/api/v1\'));\n  await tester.pumpAndSettle();\n\n  expect(tester.widget<TextF
ield>(textField).controller!.text,\n      \'http://user-input.com\');\n});\n```\
n\nThis test passes because the `BlocListener` has `listenWhen` that checks `_co
ntroller.text.isEmpty`. But wait, the comment says "Simulate load() completing a
fter user input". However, `load()` would NOT emit if `state.serverBaseUrl.isNot
Empty` (since the user already typed). So this test is simulating a direct `emit
`, not what `load()` actually does.\n\nActually, looking back at the `BlocListen
er` more carefully:\n\n```dart\nlistenWhen: (previous, current) =>\n    previous
.serverBaseUrl.isEmpty &&\n    current.serverBaseUrl.isNotEmpty &&\n    _control
ler.text.isEmpty &&\n    !_focusNode.hasFocus,\n```\n\nThis only fires when tran
sitioning from empty to non-empty. But what if there\'s a transition where `prev
ious` is non-empty and `current` is different non-empty?\n\nWait, there\'s no li
stener for that case! The `listener` only sets `_controller.text = state.serverB
aseUrl` when transitioning from empty to non-empty. So after the user has typed 
something, even if the cubit emits a different URL, the controller won\'t be upd
ated. That\'s by design.\n\nNow, let me think about what could cause "修改后仍会
