se. Even if `BlocProvider` caches the cubit in most cases, there might be edge c
ases (like during navigation, or when the app is backgrounded and foregrounded, 
or during certain animations) where the `BlocProvider` element is unmounted and 
remounted. When that happens, `create` is called again, `getIt<DevToolsCubit>()`
returns a new instance (because it\'s a factory), and `load()` fetches the URL f
rom SharedPreferences. If the URL was saved correctly, `load()` should return th
e saved URL, not the default.\n\nWait, if the URL was saved correctly to SharedP
references, then even a new cubit instance would load the correct URL. So the fa
ctory vs singleton issue wouldn\'t cause the default to be filled if the save wa
s successful.\n\nUnless... the save was NOT successful? But the bug says "修改后
" (after modifying), which suggests the user modified the input. It doesn\'t say
they saved successfully.\n\nHmm, let me re-read the bug: "Dev Tools Drawer 的 Se
rver URL 输入框修改后仍会自动填充默认地址" - "After modifying the Server URL inp
ut in Dev Tools Drawer, it still automatically fills with the default address."\
n\nThis could mean:\n1. User types a new URL\n2. The input automatically reverts
to the default address (without even saving/closing)\n\nOR it could mean:\n1. Us
er types a new URL and saves\n2. They close and reopen the drawer\n3. It shows t
he default address\n\nThe first interpretation is more consistent with "修改后仍
会自动填充" (after modifying, it still auto-fills). If it\'s happening immediate
ly after typing, that would be a more severe bug.\n\nLet me think about what cou
ld cause the text to reset while the user is typing.\n\nIn `server_url_tool.dart
`:\n```dart\nBlocListener<DevToolsCubit, DevToolsState>(\n  listenWhen: (previou
