ontext) {\n  return Semantics(\n    label: labelText ?? hintText,\n    textField
: true,\n    child: TextField(\n      controller: controller,\n      focusNode: 
focusNode,\n      ...\n      onChanged: onChanged,\n      ...\n    ),\n  );\n}\n
```\n\nIt just passes `controller` to `TextField`. No issue there.\n\nHmm, what 
if there\'s a parent widget that\'s causing `ServerUrlTool` to be recreated on e
very keystroke? No, that would require the key to change or the parent to remove
and re-add it.\n\nWait, I just thought of something. In Flutter, when a `TextFie
ld`\'s `onChanged` callback triggers a `setState` (or in this case, a cubit emit
which triggers `BlocBuilder` rebuild), the `TextField` itself rebuilds. But sinc
e it has a `controller`, it maintains its text.\n\nActually, there IS a subtle i
ssue with `TextField` and controllers. If the widget rebuilds and the `controlle
r` prop changes, the `TextField` will detach from the old controller and attach 
to the new one. But in `ServerUrlTool`, `_controller` is a `late final` field th
at\'s created in `initState` and never changes. So the same controller instance 
is always passed.\n\nLet me think about this from the perspective of what change
d in #35. In #35, they:\n1. Added a `FocusNode`\n2. Changed from `addPostFrameCa
llback` to `BlocListener` with `listenWhen`\n3. Added `focusNode` to `SwTextFiel
d`\n\nBefore #35, the issue was "输入即重置、无法复制粘贴、保存配置不生效" (typi
