mpty, and focus is not on the field.\n\nThe new code has a subtle issue. The `li
stenWhen` condition checks `!_focusNode.hasFocus`. But what if the user opens th
e drawer and the text field AUTOMATICALLY gets focus (e.g., via `autofocus` or s
ome other mechanism)? No, `SwTextField` doesn\'t have `autofocus`.\n\nWait, what
if the issue is that `BlocListener` fires when the user BLURS the field after ty
ping?\n\nScenario:\n1. User opens drawer\n2. `ServerUrlTool` created, controller
initialized with empty text\n3. `load()` hasn\'t completed yet\n4. User types "h
ttp://192.168.1.100:3000/api/v1"\n5. `onChanged` updates cubit state to the type
d URL\n6. User blurs the field (taps outside or taps save button)\n7. `load()` c
ompletes LATE. At this point, `state.serverBaseUrl` is `\'http://192.168.1.100:3
000/api/v1\'`, which is NOT empty. So `load()` does NOT emit anything.\n\nThis i
s fine.\n\nWait, what if `load()` completes BEFORE the user types anything? Let 
me trace:\n1. User opens drawer\n2. `ServerUrlTool` created, controller initiali
zed with empty text (cubit state is empty)\n3. `load()` completes, state transit
ions from empty to default URL\n4. `BlocListener` fires (because `_controller.te
xt.isEmpty && !_focusNode.hasFocus`), controller gets default URL\n5. User modif
ies the URL\n6. User saves\n7. User closes drawer\n8. User opens drawer\n9. `Ser
verUrlTool` recreated, `initState` reads cubit state (saved URL)\n10. Controller
initialized with saved URL\n\nThis should also be fine.\n\nWhat if the bug is th
at `BlocProvider` creates a new cubit when `DevToolsWrapper` rebuilds? Let me ch
eck if there\'s any condition under which `BlocProvider` would be unmounted.\n\n
Actually, I just had a breakthrough. Let me look at `BlocProvider`\'s behavior m
ore carefully.\n\nIn `flutter_bloc` v8.1.6, `BlocProvider` extends `SingleChildS
tatelessWidget`. Its `buildWithChild` returns an `InheritedProvider`. When the `
BlocProvider` widget is rebuilt (e.g., parent rebuilds), a new `InheritedProvide
r` widget is created. But the old `InheritedProvider` element is updated.\n\nHow
ever, there\'s an important detail: in some versions of the `provider` package, 
if the `create` callback changes, it doesn\'t matter because `create` is only ca
lled once.\n\nSo the cubit should persist.\n\nBut wait, I just realized: what if
the issue is NOT about the cubit being recreated, but about `DevToolsRepository`
returning the default URL?\n\nLooking at `DevToolsRepositoryImpl`:\n```dart\n@ov
erride\nFuture<String> getServerBaseUrl() async {\n  final prefs = await _prefsI
nstance;\n  return prefs.getString(_key) ?? _default;\n}\n```\n\nIf `SharedPrefe
rences` doesn\'t have the key, it returns `_default`. But if the user saved succ
essfully, the key should exist.\n\nWhat if the save didn\'t work? Looking at `sa
ve()`:\n```dart\nFuture<void> save() async {\n  final error = _validateUrl(state
